nodes.bodyText:
I would move it to constructor and made all fields non-statc final.
Constructor would try to initialize objects fields:

first it would call Globals.getDefaultHabitat() - it does not try to initialize the service loader and can return null.
if the loader is null, set all services to null (final)
else

init all services via calls to private static method with API



<T> T findService(ServiceLocator locator, Class<T> clazz) {
  if (locator == null) {
    return null;
  } 
  ServiceHandle<RequestTracingService> handle = locator.getServiceHandle(clazz);
  if (handle != null && handle.isActive()) {
    return handle.getService();
  }
  return null;
}



Then created isTracingAvailable() returning true ONLY if all services were initialized.
getter will be only getters
I would remove the serviceLoader field - all usages would use Globals directly, but only after checking isTracingAvailable() is true
create yet getDeployment() getter
THEN

JerseyOpenTracingAutoDiscoverable can use new PayaraTracingServices.isTracingAvailable and getDeployment
JaxrsClientBuilderDecorator.requestTracingPresent can simply return new PayaraTracingServices().isTracingAvailable instead of it's current body.
service locator is not needed from PayaraTracingservices any more.

